The father of Chelsea captain John Terry has told how his son was a ‘tower of strength’ who had 'been through it as well' after being cleared of a race-hate charge in his latest brush with the law.

Ted Terry, 59, had been accused of headbutting Amarjit Talafair and calling him a ‘f****** P***’ after a drunken row over a cigarette.

Speaking outside court Terry said he felt 'relieved' at the verdict – which came less than two years after his professional footballer son was also cleared of racial abuse.

