A jury of seven men and five women took an hour and 20 minutes to find self-employed decorator Terry not guilty of one count of racially-aggravated common assault after a five-day trial.

Terry, from Grays in Essex, was also cleared of one count of racially-aggravated fear or provocation of violence.

His colleagues, Stephen Niland, 36, and Moldova-born Tudor Musteata, 47, were also found not guilty of racially-aggravated fear or provocation of violence.

